This paper presents a planning framework for a bipedal robot in complex environments, which involves collision checking, dynamic and kinematic constraints, and sampling-based planning algorithms. These topics are all related to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for obstacle detection and avoidance, and the application of control theory (cs.SY) for generating full body dynamic walking behavior. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of machine learning (cs.LG) for learning the dynamics of the bipedal robot.
